<br>
We started with 24 people, and when we finished clearing, we had 12, so my role was as diversified as it can be.<br>
<br>
For most of the night, I was able to use my pet, so I had to be mindful of him.  We had only one shaman, so I was on malise duty -- which is easier in fear than it is in hate.  <br>
<br>
Malise duty consists of casting the highest level spell you have in the malise line you have.  Once a monster is malised, you have you announce it to the raid with an ooc social that spits out something like, &quot;===MALISEMENT===&quot;.  This is an easy job, but you have to learn which monsters you can malise easily, and which monsters to give up easily on. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You can also start malising mez'd monsters before combat is initiated on them.<br>
<br>
Along with all of this, I was also nuking for a good part of the night.  Later on, with our numbers low, I was put on modrod duty, making sure there were plenty of mod rods on the ground for clerics and encs to use.  Our main cleric has that blue kunark ruby bp clone that regens, so it worked out nicely.  I had a bard in my group with manasong 2, and an enc casting clarity 2 on me, so it worked out nicely.<br>
<br>
This doesn't sound like a lot of work, but you have to switch between two or three sets of hotkeys pretty quickly, and with the modrod duty, I was kept really busy.<br>
<br>
That was the most fun I've had in Hate.  I really enjoyed being part of a small group, and I enjoy being on malise duty..  It beats just medding and nuking throughout the night.<br>
<br>
 <p>Vylaek<BR>
Dark Elf Magician<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usilvara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/1/00 1:35:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gol.tux.dk/images/Silvara.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Request for &quot;Alternate plane mage behaviour guide&q</span><hr size=1> Fear<br>
<br>
Like they said above, expect to die, sometimes a lot.  It depends upon how good your raid leader is and how well the party works as a team, how many enchanters you have, and some luck.  As mages we have mostly taken over the Malosi role in raids but coordinate with any shamans, never hurts to have 2 people doing it.  Fire can be used on all the mobs here.  I also do not turn off taunt, any damage my pet can take is less for the tanks, I get summoned a lot but rarely get hurt.<br>
<br>
Hate.<br>
<br>
After the party gets set in their camp you can pet up.  Keep a close eye on your pet and be ready to have it bach off if it starts to run.  When fighting Spites, if your the only mage there, assist the spite, and do damage shields on the tanks.  You really need more than 1 person doing Malosi here as you will get resisted a lot.  After Malosi fire is good here also, if you are fighting near a wall you can go up the wall a little ways and use Lava Bolt.<br>
<br>
Dragons,<br>
<br>
Can't give any advice here, used to be on Veeshan and FoH aleays took the dragons, now on Saryrn but level 55 and can't do them<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://gol.tux.dk/images/Silv_Signature.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubrene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/1/00 3:45:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Request for &quot;Alternate plane mage behaviour guide&q</span><hr size=1> Abyen!<br>
